6
00:00:23.020 --> 00:00:24.570
So, what is a relational database?

7
00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:29.420
A relational database is a database
structured to recognize relationships

8
00:00:29.420 --> 00:00:31.910
among stored items of information.

9
00:00:31.910 --> 00:00:35.250
This type of database will have data sets
that are linked through relationships

10
00:00:35.250 --> 00:00:36.630
stored within the data model.

11
00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:43.110
MySQL, Oracle and SQL Server are all
examples of relational database software.

12
00:00:44.220 --> 00:00:47.230
A relational database can also
be any file that has data in it.

13
00:00:48.340 --> 00:00:50.140
The next big question is,

14
00:00:50.140 --> 00:00:53.560
why would someone be interested
in using a relational database?

15
00:00:53.560 --> 00:00:57.130
Today's organizations all have
access to huge amounts of data.

16
00:00:57.130 --> 00:01:00.590
And the amount of information collected
on a daily basis continues to grow.

17
00:01:01.590 --> 00:01:05.760
Saving data provides organizations,
the ability to automate their tasks and

18
00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:06.870
