21
00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:17.910
This can lead to better decisions, but
it is also the keystone for automation.

22
00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:22.602
Often times related data is
stored in different data sets.

23
00:01:22.602 --> 00:01:27.530
For example, one data set may store a
customer's name, phone number and address.

24
00:01:27.530 --> 00:01:30.700
While another might store the transactions
made by that same customer.

25
00:01:31.700 --> 00:01:33.110
In real business environments,

26
00:01:33.110 --> 00:01:37.660
many different data sets are needed to
be combined to drive business insights.

27
00:01:37.660 --> 00:01:40.480
For example, business analytics can be

28
00:01:40.480 --> 00:01:44.000
used on customer data to predict
future purchasing behaviors.

29
00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.790
Or analyzing inventory trends can lead
